page.title: 09DAILY ROUTINES
page.content: On Sunday morning I woke up at nine fifteen. I had my breakfast and then I had my hair washed. At eleven o clock I went to Sunday School, at twelve I came home. I had my dinner and then I got ready for the Clayton Frickley Horse Show. At about quarter to two we set off for the Horse Show. When we got there I entered straight away for the potato race, it was quite good fun. After the show we had our tea and then I went out to play with my friend Sharon. We played outside for about thirty minutes. At ten past eight I came in for my Supper and watched television, at twenty to ten I went to bed. It had been quite an exciting and enjoyable day.
